commit message: Clean up some debug prints.

Do a little extra work to extract pixels correctly from aligned words in the pixel buffer.

Apparently, one way ARM can handle unaligned memory accesses is to just align
them for you.
Allow external binary to just return true, move native testForSu to the Service, move root checks to a .Utils class.
Add Prefs to the .Util package.
Fix a bug that would turn pixels blue.
Fix lost import from moving the Prefs class.
Add API to AndroSSService for changing the output directory.
Redo MoreSettings as a PreferenceActivity. Changing output dir not yet working.
Add missing xml for MoreSettings.
Use stdint types more consistently in pixel formatting code.
Fix the signature of the testForSu native function.
Move some strings out of Java files and into strings.xml, and update their text.
Compile native code -Wall -Wextra -Werror and fix issues exposed by them.
Update AndroSSNative from the last commit.
Make some of the bitwork in extractPixel a little more readable.
Move de-base64'ing of the external binary into its own function so testForSu can do it, too.
Merge branch Atrix_support.
Correctly drop garbage from fbread.
Don't show root popups unless we're on a GENERIC device.
Disable irrelevant 'Retry root check' option in (More) Settings.
Have DebugInfo show the param string straight from fbread on Tegra devices.
Add correct output dir changing.
Compile native code -O3.
Fix an NPE when changing output dirs.
Populate the change output dir popup with the current directory when it's first created.
Allow the Service to return the configured output dir before init().
Fix Tegra detection by using stat instead of system().

Switch to manual pipe/fork/dup2/exec for capturing stderr from fbread.

Android's sh doesn't seem to do 2>&1 >/dev/null reliably.
Release v0.3.
